Definition of Done 2.0

1. The completion of a feature fulfilling the basic requirements outlined.
2. The successful implementation of a feature, which functions without any bugs or errors arising.
3. The appUser being able to make use of the feature without needing to refer to technical documentation.
4. The feature making use of common web-based appUser behaviour and traits so it feels fluid and familiar to a appUser.
5. The appearance of the feature within the greater program possessing clear text and widgets with enough contrast so it can be viewed without difficulty.
